Text.Value: Why bother to tell you this, though? You surely can't understand.
I remember finding you close to death, beaten black and blue on the floor of this sanctum. It must have been a few hours after the tadpole was placed in your skull.
This won't hurt a bit, though I don't suppose you can feel much now, anyway.
The most important work, the nature of which I only heard whispers of.
Play dumb - let her believe you lost your wits along with your memory.
I don't know what you're talking about, but you're going to tell me everything.
Wait... By the Bone Lord, it's you!
Poor, stupid thing. Why is it even here? I thought we sent its pod away so it could be used elsewhere.
Did... you... hurt... me...?
*Her experiments may well have made the damage worse.*
My mind may be gone, but my blade is sharp!
This is where I was left after someone infected me?
*You were no Myrkul cultist, that much is sure. You sense in your soul you were something far greater.*
Scowl: She didn't do a great job of fixing me.
I kept you as mine until you were needed by our superiors.
Oh, but what an arresting voice you have!
Missed you...
It has never been the same with another... All the other victims who come here just meekly obey. You thrashed, you fought, you were indomitable.
Ketheric needed me? For what?
Truthfully, I'm not surprised to see you found your way back here all by yourself. I always knew you were clever.
I wanted to keep you for myself but they shipped you away.
Keep me? What did you do to me?
You talk? And you are aware? How is that possible?
*Someone else must have attacked you, in the midst of whatever you were doing down here.*
I thought I'd never see you again ...

EditorData.NodeContext: Overjoyed, happy to see you again

Text.Value: You will die for what you did to me.
Bone Lord... you're the perfect man... All that is unnecessary stripped away... Primal... innocent... pure...
Bone Lord... you're the perfect woman... All that is unnecessary stripped away... Primal... innocent... pure...
Bone Lord... you're the perfect being... All that is unnecessary stripped away... Primal... innocent... pure...
Lashers... bring this one back to my table! And prepare my knives for a long night of experiments!
Try to remember the attack.
Something must have gone wrong for you to have wandered all the way back here... even if it is pleasant to be reunited.
*She is but the hack-doctor who half-pieced you together, after whatever caused your head to get in this mess.*
Oh, it pains to hear you speak such words against one who adored tending to you so.
You talk? How is that possible? Something must've gone wrong.
Who was I to you when I was here? Before I was infected?
How you got here was a total mystery, but I stitched you up just enough to keep you alive, then placed you within your crib.
You were my very first, after all. I learnt everything about the parasites from you.
Adorable... I did miss it. Its simplicity, its fear, it thrashing its own head against its pod, cracking its skull again and again in a futile attempt to escape.
But as special as you are, you shouldn't be swanning around here, acting as if free will is yours again.
*This necromancer was a grunt in the scheme of the horrors enacted against you. That attacker is the source.*
I was not behind it - I do not know. But whoever did it, I'm so glad they left you here for me.
We're going to kill you, sweet one. But I promise I will stay with you afterwards.
*In the heart of all these membranes, there was a dagger awaiting you all along. But from who?*
We had such a close bond. I opened you up endlessly with my scalpels, and got lost in your insides.
Ponder why you were down here before.
Move on.
You're not supposed to be here, special one. That's not right. But I don't want to damage you.
How precious - sweeter than any man who still has his brain! The things I'd do with you, if I were in command of the parasite piloting you.
How precious - sweeter than any woman who still has her brain! The things I'd do with you, if I were in command of the parasite piloting you.
How precious - sweeter than any person who still has their brain! The things I'd do with you, if I were in command of the parasite piloting you.
I think we have to put you down, though, dear one.
Urgh, Lashers, Balthazar let one of his walking carcasses lapse from his control... Let's ferry them back.

Synopsis:
Krustine, the Mistress of Souls in the Colony Barracks, recognizes the Dark Urge.
She previously watched over the Dark Urge in their pod and became obsessed with them.
